## Assumptions

- Providers might be hostile
  - might cheat about resources
  - might tamper with requestor's payloads
- Providers might not be reliable
- Requestors might be hostile
  - might cheat about payments
  - might wish to attack provider infrastructure
- Requestors might want decent quality of services
- Some requestors might want to use only specific providers
  - e.g. those they trust not to attack their payloads and data
  - e.g. those they have a (outside protocol) business relationship
- Some providers might want to serve only specific requestors
  - e.g. those they trust not to attack their infrastructure
  - e.g. those they have a (outside protocol) business relationship
